1
00:01:35,520 --> 00:01:37,440
What kind of cuisine does Chef Jiao make?

2
00:01:37,440 --> 00:01:38,570
As soon as I arrived,

3
00:01:38,680 --> 00:01:40,680
he asked me to cut Wensi Tofu for him.

4
00:01:40,920 --> 00:01:43,250
Chef Jiao must be a Huaiyang cuisine chef.

5
00:01:43,640 --> 00:01:45,100
Who are the guests coming?

6
00:01:45,200 --> 00:01:46,259
Did you ask around?

7
00:01:46,479 --> 00:01:47,200
I did.

8
00:01:47,360 --> 00:01:48,280
Sibao told me.

9
00:01:49,240 --> 00:01:51,280
There's a writer

10
00:01:51,800 --> 00:01:52,960
surnamed Jin.

11
00:01:53,360 --> 00:01:55,320
Then there is a president

12
00:01:55,560 --> 00:01:57,690
of some literati chamber of commerce.

13
00:01:57,920 --> 00:01:59,080
And there is a foreigner

14
00:01:59,080 --> 00:02:00,640
who likes Chinese culture.

15
00:02:01,320 --> 00:02:03,840
Have the rules for your cooking competition been set?

16
00:02:03,840 --> 00:02:04,400
Yes.

17
00:02:04,520 --> 00:02:05,640
Four dishes.

18
00:02:05,880 --> 00:02:06,840
Four dishes.

19
00:02:07,800 --> 00:02:09,160
Four dishes and one soup.

20
00:02:09,160 --> 00:02:10,080
There's a soup.

21
00:02:11,080 --> 00:02:13,240
Four dishes, one soup, and one dessert.

22
00:02:13,240 --> 00:02:14,800
Can you finish your sentence in one breath?

23
00:02:14,800 --> 00:02:15,880
I'm done.

24
00:02:17,560 --> 00:02:19,690
Chef Jiao is good at Huaiyang cuisine.

25
00:02:20,200 --> 00:02:24,060
The characteristic of Huaiyang cuisine is light and original taste.

26
00:02:24,840 --> 00:02:26,120
The literati like it.

27
00:02:28,200 --> 00:02:29,720
What are the dishes in Huaiyang cuisine?

28
00:02:29,720 --> 00:02:31,579
Braised Meatballs with Crab Roe,

29
00:02:32,520 --> 00:02:34,120
Boiled Shredded Dried Tofu,

30
00:02:34,120 --> 00:02:35,960
Stir-fried Shrimps in Egg White,

31
00:02:35,960 --> 00:02:37,020
Soft-Stirred Eel.

32
00:02:37,040 --> 00:02:38,640
You know all of these, right?

33
00:02:38,720 --> 00:02:40,680
Then Chef Jiao's four dishes and one soup

34
00:02:40,680 --> 00:02:42,280
must be within this range.

35
00:02:42,760 --> 00:02:45,280
These literati and wealthy merchants

36
00:02:45,480 --> 00:02:46,640
are well-informed

37
00:02:46,680 --> 00:02:48,040
and used to socializing.

38
00:02:48,040 --> 00:02:49,320
For Huaiyang cuisine,

39
00:02:49,480 --> 00:02:50,880
it must be a common sight.

40
00:02:50,880 --> 00:02:53,280
Common means ordinary.

41
00:02:53,720 --> 00:02:56,120
Ordinary may mean mediocre.

42
00:02:56,880 --> 00:02:58,760
He can't come up with anything new.

43
00:02:58,760 --> 00:02:59,560
Wanfu,

44
00:03:00,160 --> 00:03:01,720
Chef Jiao might not win,

45
00:03:02,040 --> 00:03:03,360
and you might not lose.

46
00:03:03,600 --> 00:03:04,320
Really?

47
00:03:04,680 --> 00:03:07,040
Since Chef Jiao is taking the southern cuisine route,

48
00:03:07,040 --> 00:03:09,080
you should focus on northern cuisine.

49
00:03:09,080 --> 00:03:11,140
What northern dishes are you good at?

50
00:03:13,160 --> 00:03:15,200
I only know some home-style dishes.

51
00:03:16,000 --> 00:03:18,730
They are just common dishes for ordinary people.

52
00:03:19,200 --> 00:03:21,200
That's hard to present at a banquet.

53
00:03:21,240 --> 00:03:22,700
Think about my dish names,

54
00:03:23,200 --> 00:03:24,860
like Deep-fried Pan Jinlian,

55
00:03:25,120 --> 00:03:26,400
Stir-fried Ximen Qing,

56
00:03:26,400 --> 00:03:27,930
these are not presentable.

57
00:03:28,280 --> 00:03:30,010
What is Stir-fried Ximen Qing?

58
00:03:31,800 --> 00:03:33,460
It's Stir-fried Pork Kidney.

59
00:03:34,160 --> 00:03:36,760
In some places, beef kidneys and sheep kidneys

60
00:03:36,960 --> 00:03:38,600
are both called Stir-fried Ximen Qing.

61
00:03:38,600 --> 00:03:40,200
What about Deep-fried Pan Jinlian?

62
00:03:40,200 --> 00:03:42,000
It is made of egg whites and flour

63
00:03:42,040 --> 00:03:43,040
mixed into a batter,

64
00:03:43,040 --> 00:03:44,760
and pumpkin flowers

65
00:03:44,880 --> 00:03:45,940
deep-fried in oil.

66
00:03:46,000 --> 00:03:47,840
That is Deep-fried Pan Jinlian.

67
00:03:50,440 --> 00:03:52,370
It's indeed not very presentable,

68
00:03:52,800 --> 00:03:53,280
right?

69
00:03:53,440 --> 00:03:54,440
Wanfu.

70
00:03:57,560 --> 00:03:59,079
Can you cook fish?

71
00:03:59,440 --> 00:04:00,120
Yes.

72
00:04:00,320 --> 00:04:02,450
Mandarin fish, carp, yellow croaker,

73
00:04:02,480 --> 00:04:03,640
steamed, braised,

74
00:04:03,800 --> 00:04:04,440
stewed, or boiled,

75
00:04:04,440 --> 00:04:05,400
I can do them all.

76
00:04:08,480 --> 00:04:09,720
Then

77
00:04:10,760 --> 00:04:12,600
let's serve him a dish of

78
00:04:12,800 --> 00:04:15,160
Lingzhao Mandarin Fish.

79
00:04:17,079 --> 00:04:18,120
What is Lingzhao?

80
00:04:18,279 --> 00:04:20,279
Lingzhao is not a thing.

81
00:04:20,800 --> 00:04:21,860
Lingzhao is a place

82
00:04:21,880 --> 00:04:24,760
of imperial grace.

83
00:04:25,160 --> 00:04:27,440
Back then, King Wen of Zhou

84
00:04:27,640 --> 00:04:29,200
shared his joy with the people

85
00:04:29,200 --> 00:04:30,960
and was deeply loved.

86
00:04:31,480 --> 00:04:32,280
So,

87
00:04:32,520 --> 00:04:35,440
he called the pond the Numinous Pond.

88
00:04:36,280 --> 00:04:38,800
The more, the merrier.

89
00:04:39,240 --> 00:04:40,600
It fits his intention perfectly.

90
00:04:40,600 --> 00:04:41,280
So,

91
00:04:41,640 --> 00:04:45,640
this dish is called Lingzhao Mandarin Fish.

92
00:04:46,840 --> 00:04:47,720
Master.

93
00:04:48,360 --> 00:04:49,760
Why are your words always

94
00:04:50,000 --> 00:04:51,680
winding and twisting?

95
00:04:51,680 --> 00:04:52,880
I don't understand.

96
00:04:53,560 --> 00:04:54,800
Does all that you just said

97
00:04:54,800 --> 00:04:56,040
mean we're just giving

98
00:04:56,040 --> 00:04:57,320
Braised Mandarin Fish

99
00:04:57,640 --> 00:04:58,480
a new name?

100
00:05:00,200 --> 00:05:02,040
My old habit flared up again.

101
00:05:03,840 --> 00:05:06,240
My words are difficult to pronounce again.

102
00:05:06,560 --> 00:05:07,280
Okay.

103
00:05:07,640 --> 00:05:10,320
Then I'll say something you can understand.

104
00:05:12,120 --> 00:05:13,920
These scholars and writers

105
00:05:14,120 --> 00:05:16,640
always like to, while eating and drinking,

106
00:05:16,680 --> 00:05:18,640
discussing classics and philosophies,

107
00:05:18,640 --> 00:05:21,720
to prove they are not ordinary people.

108
00:05:22,240 --> 00:05:24,800
It's clearly just food to fill the stomach,

109
00:05:25,040 --> 00:05:28,400
but they insist it's spiritual nourishment.

110
00:05:28,880 --> 00:05:29,880
Since they are like this,

111
00:05:29,880 --> 00:05:31,810
we'll cater to their preferences.

112
00:05:33,800 --> 00:05:35,000
How about organizing

113
00:05:36,920 --> 00:05:39,280
a Meng Family Banquet?

114
00:05:40,640 --> 00:05:42,280
Meng Family Banquet.

115
00:05:43,320 --> 00:05:44,850
Father, this is a good idea.

116
00:05:45,640 --> 00:05:46,520
Wanfu.

117
00:05:46,760 --> 00:05:50,000
What seasonal dishes are you good at

118
00:05:50,120 --> 00:05:52,440
that are suitable to eat now?

119
00:05:53,040 --> 00:05:53,800
Yes,

120
00:05:54,120 --> 00:05:55,320
there are quite a few.

121
00:05:55,400 --> 00:05:56,680
Like Wild Rice Stem,

122
00:05:56,840 --> 00:05:57,880
Cattail,

123
00:05:58,200 --> 00:05:59,200
Walnut Kernel,

124
00:05:59,360 --> 00:06:00,000
Cicada Nymph,

125
00:06:00,000 --> 00:06:00,880
they all work.

126
00:06:01,080 --> 00:06:03,960
It is said in 'Book of Songs: Major Odes: Han Yi',

127
00:06:04,640 --> 00:06:08,300
'What are the vegetables? There are bamboo shoots and cattails.'

128
00:06:08,920 --> 00:06:10,320
Cattail is good.

129
00:06:11,040 --> 00:06:12,100
Father, am I right?

130
00:06:12,760 --> 00:06:14,440
Indeed.

131
00:06:14,680 --> 00:06:16,340
What's so good about Cattail?

132
00:06:16,800 --> 00:06:18,680
Cattail is just a vegetable that our common people

133
00:06:18,680 --> 00:06:20,160
when they want to have a feast,

134
00:06:20,160 --> 00:06:21,680
scoop out of the river,

135
00:06:22,080 --> 00:06:23,010
boil into a soup,

136
00:06:23,160 --> 00:06:24,760
and use to fool their mouths.

137
00:06:24,880 --> 00:06:26,240
What's so precious about it?

138
00:06:26,240 --> 00:06:29,570
But isn't it precious once you link it to 'The Book of Songs'?

139
00:06:30,000 --> 00:06:30,680
Come here.

140
00:06:34,880 --> 00:06:35,880
Read after me.

141
00:06:37,200 --> 00:06:39,060
It is said in 'Major Odes: Han Yi'.

142
00:06:39,480 --> 00:06:41,280
'Major Odes: Han Yi'.

143
00:06:42,240 --> 00:06:43,720
What is the relationship between these three people?

144
00:06:43,720 --> 00:06:44,450
Which three?

145
00:06:44,600 --> 00:06:46,360
Greater Court Hymns, Han Yi, and You Yun.

146
00:06:46,360 --> 00:06:47,440
Who told you they are people?

147
00:06:47,440 --> 00:06:48,600
They are not people.

148
00:06:49,159 --> 00:06:49,920
Not people?

149
00:06:50,200 --> 00:06:51,600
'The Book of Songs' has Feng, Ya, and Song.

150
00:06:51,600 --> 00:06:53,040
Ya is divided into Greater Court Hymns and Lesser Court Hymns.

151
00:06:53,040 --> 00:06:55,880
This Greater Court Hymns is the Ya in 'The Book of Songs'.

152
00:06:55,880 --> 00:06:56,940
Do you understand?

153
00:06:58,159 --> 00:06:59,880
Han Yi is one of the poems.

154
00:07:00,200 --> 00:07:02,840
'Youyun' means it says this.

155
00:07:02,960 --> 00:07:04,000
It means this.

156
00:07:04,080 --> 00:07:04,520
So it is said.

157
00:07:04,520 --> 00:07:05,120
No.

158
00:07:05,200 --> 00:07:05,760
Youyun.

159
00:07:05,960 --> 00:07:07,800
Isn't Youyun a girl's name?

160
00:07:08,040 --> 00:07:09,400
How could it be a girl?

161
00:07:09,720 --> 00:07:11,320
What is in your head?

162
00:07:12,800 --> 00:07:13,760
'Yun' means 'yue'.

163
00:07:13,760 --> 00:07:14,600
'Yue' means 'dao'.

164
00:07:14,600 --> 00:07:15,360
'Dao' means 'shuo'.

165
00:07:15,360 --> 00:07:16,200
They all mean 'to say'.

166
00:07:16,200 --> 00:07:17,200
No, no, no.

167
00:07:17,440 --> 00:07:18,970
How could 'yun' mean 'say'?

168
00:07:19,040 --> 00:07:19,800
Why not?

169
00:07:19,920 --> 00:07:21,160
Clouds float in the sky.

170
00:07:21,160 --> 00:07:21,920
How could it mean 'say'?

171
00:07:21,920 --> 00:07:23,800
That's how the ancients used it.

172
00:07:23,840 --> 00:07:24,840
They didn't use 'shuo'.

173
00:07:24,840 --> 00:07:26,720
They used 'yun', 'yue', and 'dao'.

174
00:07:26,720 --> 00:07:28,050
They didn't use 'shuo'.

175
00:07:28,200 --> 00:07:28,680
Well...

176
00:07:30,200 --> 00:07:31,600
It'll wake the child.

177
00:07:32,800 --> 00:07:34,000
This treasure book.

178
00:07:34,440 --> 00:07:36,080
Everything is in it.

179
00:07:36,440 --> 00:07:37,800
Look carefully.

180
00:07:43,080 --> 00:07:44,540
Here, take your medicine.

181
00:07:44,960 --> 00:07:45,960
Nurse Han.

182
00:07:46,360 --> 00:07:47,240
I'm done here.

183
00:07:47,440 --> 00:07:48,400
Okay.

184
00:07:50,480 --> 00:07:51,610
Hurry up and take it.

185
00:07:55,360 --> 00:07:56,440
Good for you.

186
00:07:56,800 --> 00:07:58,159
Soaking yourself in water.

187
00:07:58,159 --> 00:07:59,880
Your wound got infected and you have a fever.

188
00:07:59,880 --> 00:08:02,410
You really want to torture yourself to death.

189
00:08:07,280 --> 00:08:09,200
That you have a silver tongue,

190
00:08:09,240 --> 00:08:10,970
is known to the whole hospital.

191
00:08:17,000 --> 00:08:18,260
Here is a thermometer.

192
00:08:18,400 --> 00:08:19,720
Did you crunch it down?

193
00:08:26,320 --> 00:08:26,840
Come.

194
00:08:31,440 --> 00:08:32,840
Give me your hand.

195
00:08:44,960 --> 00:08:46,090
You actually ate it?

196
00:08:47,440 --> 00:08:48,100
Spit it out.

197
00:08:48,240 --> 00:08:48,900
Spit it out!

198
00:08:49,000 --> 00:08:50,000
Open your mouth!

199
00:08:50,480 --> 00:08:52,040
That's mercury. It's toxic.

200
00:08:52,040 --> 00:08:52,960
Open up!

201
00:08:53,640 --> 00:08:54,960
Open up!

202
00:08:55,920 --> 00:08:56,960
Spit it out now.

203
00:08:57,160 --> 00:08:57,680
Hurry!

204
00:09:04,440 --> 00:09:06,800
Why didn't you crunch it down?

205
00:09:11,320 --> 00:09:13,160
Guess you're a normal person.

206
00:09:29,280 --> 00:09:30,640
I'll ask you one last time.

207
00:09:30,640 --> 00:09:32,280
Are you going to give me the medicine?

208
00:09:32,280 --> 00:09:32,920
No.

209
00:09:33,080 --> 00:09:34,400
I've said all I can.

210
00:09:34,720 --> 00:09:36,800
If you don't give it to me, I'll take it by force!

211
00:09:36,800 --> 00:09:37,240
Give it to me!

212
00:09:37,240 --> 00:09:38,040
What are you doing?

213
00:09:38,040 --> 00:09:39,100
We were here first.

214
00:09:39,280 --> 00:09:40,360
We were here first. Why should we give it to you?

215
00:09:40,360 --> 00:09:42,280
Our Battalion Commander is taking his last breath.

216
00:09:42,280 --> 00:09:43,440
Give me the medicine. Hurry up!

217
00:09:43,440 --> 00:09:44,880
I don't care about your Battalion Commander.

218
00:09:44,880 --> 00:09:46,360
Our platoon leader is dying too.

219
00:09:46,360 --> 00:09:47,400
According to the rules,

220
00:09:47,400 --> 00:09:48,480
we have priority.

221
00:09:48,720 --> 00:09:49,760
What rules?

222
00:09:50,200 --> 00:09:52,000
Are the lives of our local troops not lives?

223
00:09:52,000 --> 00:09:52,960
Give me the medicine!

224
00:09:52,960 --> 00:09:54,600
There are only two of us left in our battalion.

225
00:09:54,600 --> 00:09:55,760
Give me the medicine!

226
00:09:55,760 --> 00:09:56,560
No!

227
00:09:58,920 --> 00:10:00,180
Don't come any closer!

228
00:10:04,600 --> 00:10:06,520
If you won't let my Battalion Commander live,

229
00:10:06,520 --> 00:10:08,680
I'll kill all of you!

230
00:10:09,800 --> 00:10:10,800
Give me the medicine!

231
00:10:10,800 --> 00:10:11,360
No.

232
00:10:11,520 --> 00:10:12,960
This medicine is for our platoon leader.

233
00:10:12,960 --> 00:10:14,160
Then I'll blow him up!

234
00:10:14,800 --> 00:10:15,400
Don't!

235
00:10:15,400 --> 00:10:16,460
What are you doing?

236
00:10:19,360 --> 00:10:21,490
Give me the medicine, I'm begging you!

237
00:10:21,560 --> 00:10:23,320
I bet you don't dare pull the pin.

238
00:10:23,320 --> 00:10:24,050
I don't dare?

239
00:10:24,480 --> 00:10:25,740
Try me and see if I dare!

240
00:10:25,840 --> 00:10:26,720
Give me the medicine!

241
00:10:26,720 --> 00:10:28,050
Just to save one person,

242
00:10:28,080 --> 00:10:29,400
you'd blow up twenty people?

243
00:10:29,400 --> 00:10:31,120
I don't care if there are twenty people.

244
00:10:31,120 --> 00:10:33,080
I just want to save my Battalion Commander.

245
00:10:33,080 --> 00:10:34,160
You want to save your Battalion Commander,

246
00:10:34,160 --> 00:10:36,560
and they want to save their platoon leader.

247
00:10:36,640 --> 00:10:37,400
I don't care!

248
00:10:37,680 --> 00:10:38,720
I don't care!

249
00:10:39,040 --> 00:10:40,520
I'm going to blow you all up!

250
00:10:40,520 --> 00:10:43,200
I'll make you all die with my Battalion Commander!

251
00:10:43,200 --> 00:10:44,320
I'll blow you up!

252
00:10:44,520 --> 00:10:45,320
I'll blow you up!

253
00:10:45,320 --> 00:10:46,720
Squad Leader of Squad Three!

254
00:10:46,720 --> 00:10:47,760
The medicine.

255
00:10:49,640 --> 00:10:50,770
Don't give it to him.

256
00:10:50,840 --> 00:10:51,840
Stop dawdling.

257
00:10:58,800 --> 00:11:00,400
Buddy, the medicine is here.

258
00:11:00,560 --> 00:11:02,160
Even if you weren't holding a grenade today,

259
00:11:02,160 --> 00:11:04,120
I'd still give you this medicine.

260
00:11:05,280 --> 00:11:07,040
But you must remember one thing.

261
00:11:07,040 --> 00:11:08,720
Everyone lying here today

262
00:11:09,040 --> 00:11:10,560
is a hero who fought on the battlefield to defend our home and country,

263
00:11:10,560 --> 00:11:12,120
fighting the Japanese.

264
00:11:12,480 --> 00:11:14,360
They are not only my brothers,

265
00:11:14,680 --> 00:11:16,560
but your brothers too.

266
00:11:17,160 --> 00:11:18,960
So you can't take a grenade

267
00:11:19,000 --> 00:11:21,360
and blow up your own brothers.

268
00:11:33,400 --> 00:11:34,530
On the battlefield,

269
00:11:34,600 --> 00:11:36,400
bullets have no eyes.

270
00:11:36,680 --> 00:11:37,400
When a bomb explodes,

271
00:11:37,400 --> 00:11:39,200
it doesn't care about your rank.

272
00:11:39,360 --> 00:11:40,640
If it's your time to die,

273
00:11:40,640 --> 00:11:42,600
you can't survive even if you want to.

274
00:11:42,600 --> 00:11:44,200
Those who die for the country

275
00:11:44,480 --> 00:11:46,040
are all equal.

276
00:11:51,360 --> 00:11:52,440
Grenades.

277
00:11:54,280 --> 00:11:56,080
Save them to fight the Japanese.

278
00:12:02,760 --> 00:12:03,690
Platoon leader!

279
00:12:07,160 --> 00:12:08,090
Platoon leader!

280
00:12:08,120 --> 00:12:09,580
Brother. Platoon leader!

281
00:12:10,120 --> 00:12:12,640
Buddy, I'm sorry.

282
00:12:15,160 --> 00:12:18,840
I finally see you.

283
00:12:20,600 --> 00:12:22,240
You did the right thing.

284
00:12:23,240 --> 00:12:24,400
If I were you,

285
00:12:26,000 --> 00:12:27,920
I would have done the same.

286
00:12:30,080 --> 00:12:31,840
Don't worry.

287
00:12:32,720 --> 00:12:34,880
I have nine lives.

288
00:12:35,840 --> 00:12:37,400
I won't die.

289
00:12:39,280 --> 00:12:42,640
But I need to ask you for a favor.

290
00:12:47,080 --> 00:12:48,080
Tell me.

291
00:12:48,680 --> 00:12:50,120
Do you remember

292
00:12:50,440 --> 00:12:52,370
San, who crossed the Yangtze River

293
00:12:52,840 --> 00:12:55,920
with us?

294
00:12:57,360 --> 00:12:59,280
If you survive,

295
00:13:00,040 --> 00:13:02,080
go to this address

296
00:13:02,800 --> 00:13:05,720
and give this to his sis.

297
00:13:06,920 --> 00:13:08,560
Tell her

298
00:13:09,440 --> 00:13:12,320
I'm sorry to her.

299
00:13:16,920 --> 00:13:17,760
Brother.

300
00:13:18,440 --> 00:13:20,240
Didn't you say you have nine lives?

301
00:13:20,240 --> 00:13:20,770
Brother.

302
00:13:20,960 --> 00:13:21,960
Doctor!

303
00:13:22,680 --> 00:13:23,640
Platoon leader!

304
00:13:23,760 --> 00:13:25,000
Doctor, I beg you.

305
00:13:25,280 --> 00:13:26,760
I'll kneel and bow to you.

306
00:13:26,840 --> 00:13:27,320
I beg you.

307
00:13:27,320 --> 00:13:28,600
I beg you.

308
00:13:29,120 --> 00:13:30,560
I'll do anything to repay you.

309
00:13:30,560 --> 00:13:31,480
Just save my brother.

310
00:13:31,480 --> 00:13:32,210
Get up first.

311
00:13:32,320 --> 00:13:33,760
Please save my brother.

312
00:13:34,000 --> 00:13:35,600
I beg you.

313
00:13:35,720 --> 00:13:36,780
Without medicine,

314
00:13:36,800 --> 00:13:38,260
there's nothing we can do.

315
00:13:51,160 --> 00:13:52,280
Use it on him.

316
00:13:53,200 --> 00:13:55,060
It's no longer needed over there.

317
00:14:08,080 --> 00:14:09,410
Inject it immediately.

318
00:14:09,560 --> 00:14:10,490
Platoon leader.

319
00:14:11,560 --> 00:14:13,800
I told you I wouldn't die.

320
00:14:14,280 --> 00:14:16,160
I have nine lives.

321
00:14:22,960 --> 00:14:24,000
Doctor.

322
00:14:25,640 --> 00:14:26,570
Platoon leader.

323
00:14:33,120 --> 00:14:35,040
Battalion Commander.

324
00:14:38,920 --> 00:14:43,400
Battalion Commander.

325
00:14:46,240 --> 00:14:49,800
I'm the only one left.

326
00:14:54,600 --> 00:14:56,960
Battalion Commander.

327
00:15:44,760 --> 00:15:46,080
We sat in a circle,

328
00:15:46,280 --> 00:15:47,080
drinking tea,

329
00:15:47,320 --> 00:15:48,580
and comforting Mr. Gu.

330
00:15:49,040 --> 00:15:52,240
We said it was just a threat from the Bureau of Investigation and Statistics.

331
00:15:52,240 --> 00:15:52,920
We told him,

332
00:15:53,080 --> 00:15:53,920
'Mr. Gu,

333
00:15:54,200 --> 00:15:55,480
you're doing this for your career,

334
00:15:55,480 --> 00:15:57,010
dealing with the Japanese,

335
00:15:57,080 --> 00:15:58,400
and we understand.'

336
00:15:58,560 --> 00:15:59,890
Before we could finish,

337
00:16:00,200 --> 00:16:03,080
something was thrown in from outside.

338
00:16:03,560 --> 00:16:05,160
I was sitting right behind Mr. Gu.

339
00:16:05,160 --> 00:16:06,220
What was thrown in?

340
00:16:06,240 --> 00:16:07,520
I was sitting behind Mr. Gu.

341
00:16:07,520 --> 00:16:09,040
What was thrown in?

342
00:16:10,120 --> 00:16:11,120
Was it a bomb?

343
00:16:11,320 --> 00:16:12,720
No, Hechen.

344
00:16:13,160 --> 00:16:14,560
It was a grenade.

345
00:16:15,200 --> 00:16:16,960
My ears are still ringing.

346
00:16:17,000 --> 00:16:17,460
Really,

347
00:16:17,600 --> 00:16:20,080
it was terrifying.

348
00:16:20,160 --> 00:16:21,080
How is Mr. Gu?

349
00:16:22,440 --> 00:16:24,120
How is Mr. Gu doing now?

350
00:16:24,360 --> 00:16:26,280
Mr. Gu is still lying in the hospital,

351
00:16:26,280 --> 00:16:28,120
his life hanging in the balance.

352
00:16:29,280 --> 00:16:31,000
I'm going to write a huge article.

353
00:16:31,000 --> 00:16:32,130
I will condemn them.

354
00:16:32,480 --> 00:16:34,740
You should get a bulletproof vest first.

355
00:16:35,560 --> 00:16:37,760
You should get your ears checked first.

356
00:16:38,160 --> 00:16:40,040
My ears don't matter, Hechen.

357
00:16:40,720 --> 00:16:41,760
I have my pen.

358
00:16:42,080 --> 00:16:43,600
My pen is my weapon.

359
00:16:44,120 --> 00:16:46,240
I advocate resisting Japan and saving the country.

360
00:16:46,240 --> 00:16:47,880
I oppose the Japanese army

361
00:16:48,120 --> 00:16:50,080
seizing private Chinese enterprises.

362
00:16:50,080 --> 00:16:53,080
And I also oppose the dictatorial government's

363
00:16:53,480 --> 00:16:55,960
indiscriminate terrorist acts

364
00:16:56,080 --> 00:16:59,280
against our own businessmen.

365
00:17:01,800 --> 00:17:03,520
Hechen.

366
00:17:05,400 --> 00:17:07,079
You're truly visionary.

367
00:17:07,960 --> 00:17:09,560
You transferred the factory early on

368
00:17:09,560 --> 00:17:10,599
through Mr. Brown

369
00:17:10,920 --> 00:17:12,380
to a foreign legal entity.

370
00:17:12,760 --> 00:17:14,359
That's completely useless.

371
00:17:16,960 --> 00:17:18,480
Useless.

372
00:17:18,960 --> 00:17:19,560
Last week,

373
00:17:19,680 --> 00:17:22,280
the Japanese Navy stormed the Pudong Soap Factory.

374
00:17:22,280 --> 00:17:23,680
They drove away all the Italians

375
00:17:23,680 --> 00:17:24,940
guarding the factory.

376
00:17:25,119 --> 00:17:27,119
They made up a bunch of baseless accusations,

377
00:17:27,119 --> 00:17:28,650
tore down the Italian flag,

378
00:17:28,760 --> 00:17:30,840
and put up military control seals again.

379
00:17:30,840 --> 00:17:31,880
Barbarians!

380
00:17:32,280 --> 00:17:34,160
Unreasonable barbarians!

381
00:17:34,520 --> 00:17:36,800
They trample on international conventions arbitrarily.

382
00:17:36,800 --> 00:17:38,880
Confiscating government assets is one thing,

383
00:17:38,880 --> 00:17:41,280
but these are clearly private enterprises of Chinese merchants.

384
00:17:41,280 --> 00:17:42,560
They use all kinds of tricks

385
00:17:42,560 --> 00:17:44,420
to enforce military management.

386
00:17:47,200 --> 00:17:48,560
Ruisheng, come here.

387
00:17:52,320 --> 00:17:53,360
Ruisheng.

388
00:17:54,000 --> 00:17:58,440
I'd like to invite Mr. Shao, President Shao, to dinner

389
00:17:59,160 --> 00:18:00,960
so we can have a good discussion.

390
00:18:01,200 --> 00:18:02,360
Let's see if we can

391
00:18:03,120 --> 00:18:05,960
unite the entire Shanghai business community

392
00:18:07,560 --> 00:18:10,880
to put pressure on the Shanghai Municipal Council in the concession,

393
00:18:10,880 --> 00:18:13,210
negotiate through diplomatic channels,

394
00:18:13,560 --> 00:18:15,200
and demand that the Japanese military

395
00:18:15,200 --> 00:18:17,930
earnestly fulfill international conventions.

396
00:18:19,480 --> 00:18:20,720
I heard a rumor.

397
00:18:23,160 --> 00:18:25,200
Recently, when Mr. Shao goes to Hongkou,

398
00:18:25,200 --> 00:18:28,520
he rides in a car from the expeditionary army headquarters.

399
00:18:28,520 --> 00:18:30,200
When passing the Waibaidu Ferry,

400
00:18:30,200 --> 00:18:31,660
he doesn't need to get off,

401
00:18:31,800 --> 00:18:34,730
nor does he have to take off his hat and bow 90 degrees.

402
00:18:44,360 --> 00:18:46,840
He's been negotiating with Hongkou all along.

403
00:18:46,840 --> 00:18:48,240
This is inevitable.

404
00:18:49,160 --> 00:18:51,320
Mr. Shao alone has five factories.

405
00:18:51,560 --> 00:18:53,160
In South Market and Zhabei,

406
00:18:53,280 --> 00:18:54,740
the military is in charge.

407
00:18:54,880 --> 00:18:58,480
There are plenty of people who suffered greater losses than him.

408
00:18:58,760 --> 00:19:00,200
If we talk to them one by one,

409
00:19:00,200 --> 00:19:01,530
what results can we get?

410
00:19:01,880 --> 00:19:03,320
He is the President of the Chamber of Commerce,

411
00:19:03,320 --> 00:19:04,920
holding a pivotal position.

412
00:19:05,680 --> 00:19:06,740
To unite everyone,

413
00:19:06,960 --> 00:19:09,000
only if he takes the lead,

414
00:19:09,200 --> 00:19:10,530
will it be justifiable.

415
00:19:16,000 --> 00:19:17,520
I understand you, Hechen.

416
00:19:18,480 --> 00:19:22,080
After all, you have so many industries on hand.

417
00:19:26,120 --> 00:19:27,760
The rest doesn't matter much.

418
00:19:27,760 --> 00:19:29,490
What I am most unwilling to lose

419
00:19:29,720 --> 00:19:30,920
are two factories.

420
00:19:31,360 --> 00:19:32,490
Pudong Soap Factory

421
00:19:33,280 --> 00:19:36,520
is the first factory my brother founded.

422
00:19:36,880 --> 00:19:38,240
And the other one

423
00:19:38,640 --> 00:19:40,000
is my machinery plant.

424
00:19:40,600 --> 00:19:41,520
I know.

425
00:19:42,040 --> 00:19:44,440
There are 12 private shipyards in Shanghai

426
00:19:44,720 --> 00:19:46,800
that have already been confiscated by the Japanese.

427
00:19:46,800 --> 00:19:48,120
These factories are currently,

428
00:19:48,120 --> 00:19:50,400
nominally under military management.

429
00:19:50,840 --> 00:19:52,000
But in reality,

430
00:19:52,200 --> 00:19:53,800
they are under military control

431
00:19:53,800 --> 00:19:56,000
and have secretly started operations.

432
00:19:56,080 --> 00:19:57,680
They are building warships.

433
00:19:59,200 --> 00:20:01,600
Hechen, think about it.

434
00:20:01,840 --> 00:20:03,100
Your machinery plant,

435
00:20:03,400 --> 00:20:05,130
once it falls into their hands,

436
00:20:05,200 --> 00:20:07,240
with just a little modification,

437
00:20:07,640 --> 00:20:09,440
will become a military factory.

438
00:20:14,240 --> 00:20:16,080
Actually, the most crucial thing

439
00:20:16,080 --> 00:20:18,040
is that these two factories are my roots.

440
00:20:18,040 --> 00:20:18,880
If my roots are gone,

441
00:20:18,880 --> 00:20:20,480
the building will collapse.

442
00:20:21,240 --> 00:20:22,900
I will likely lose everything

443
00:20:23,040 --> 00:20:25,560
and even end up on the streets.

444
00:20:27,440 --> 00:20:29,480
They absolutely cannot fall into the hands of the Japanese.

445
00:20:29,480 --> 00:20:30,440
I understand.

446
00:20:31,640 --> 00:20:32,520
Hechen,

447
00:20:32,920 --> 00:20:34,320
let me make my stance clear.

448
00:20:34,320 --> 00:20:35,780
I absolutely support you.

449
00:20:35,800 --> 00:20:38,040
You go invite Mr. Shao and Mr. Brown,

450
00:20:38,080 --> 00:20:39,480
and I will accompany you.

451
00:20:39,760 --> 00:20:41,960
If there is anything you can't say then,

452
00:20:42,280 --> 00:20:43,880
I'll take the lead and say it.

453
00:21:18,200 --> 00:21:18,920
Mr. Shao.

454
00:21:20,520 --> 00:21:21,240
Hechen,

455
00:21:21,520 --> 00:21:22,600
it's been a while.

456
00:21:22,840 --> 00:21:25,300
We've been looking forward to your arrival.

457
00:21:26,800 --> 00:21:28,000
Let me introduce you.

458
00:21:29,320 --> 00:21:30,880
Lin Changgeng, Mr. Lin.

459
00:21:31,160 --> 00:21:33,280
This is Mr. Tian.

460
00:21:33,960 --> 00:21:35,720
Mr. Tian, I've heard a lot about you.

461
00:21:35,720 --> 00:21:36,650
Nice to meet you.

462
00:21:37,000 --> 00:21:37,530
Mr. Shao.

463
00:21:37,640 --> 00:21:39,970
Mr. Brown and Ruisheng have both arrived.

464
00:21:40,960 --> 00:21:41,960
Mr. Shao, Mr. Lin.

465
00:21:42,080 --> 00:21:42,600
Nice to meet you.

466
00:21:42,600 --> 00:21:43,560
Please come in.

467
00:21:43,600 --> 00:21:44,520
Okay.

468
00:21:44,600 --> 00:21:45,080
Please.

469
00:22:00,200 --> 00:22:01,000
Wanfu.

470
00:22:02,080 --> 00:22:05,840
Go blanch the eel, remove the bones, and get rid of the fishy smell.

471
00:22:05,920 --> 00:22:07,040
Chef Jiao, my pan is just getting hot.

472
00:22:07,040 --> 00:22:08,300
I'm about to stir-fry.

473
00:22:08,680 --> 00:22:10,000
Move the pan away.

474
00:22:21,600 --> 00:22:22,920
Chef Jiao, it's time to serve the hot dishes.

475
00:22:22,920 --> 00:22:23,780
Are they ready?

476
00:22:23,960 --> 00:22:25,960
Okay, they will be ready in a moment.

477
00:22:26,800 --> 00:22:28,040
Wanfu, what about you?

478
00:22:28,040 --> 00:22:28,640
Me?

479
00:22:28,840 --> 00:22:30,080
Right away.

480
00:22:31,760 --> 00:22:32,520
Wanfu,

481
00:22:33,000 --> 00:22:34,240
hurry up.

482
00:22:34,440 --> 00:22:36,000
You can wait, but the food can't.

483
00:22:36,000 --> 00:22:37,520
If serving is slow and the dishes get cold,

484
00:22:37,520 --> 00:22:39,560
don't embarrass Mr. Tian then.

485
00:22:39,720 --> 00:22:41,000
Understood.

486
00:22:47,760 --> 00:22:50,820
These are the final terms from the Japanese merchants.

487
00:22:51,440 --> 00:22:54,440
All Chinese private enterprises

488
00:22:54,920 --> 00:22:56,780
managed by the Japanese military

489
00:22:56,800 --> 00:23:00,200
must resume work with the assistance of Japanese merchants.

490
00:23:00,360 --> 00:23:02,720
All costs required to resume work

491
00:23:03,000 --> 00:23:04,860
will be borne by the Chinese side.

492
00:23:05,200 --> 00:23:07,680
As for the profits after resuming production,

493
00:23:07,680 --> 00:23:10,800
the Japanese merchants will get 51 percent,

494
00:23:10,960 --> 00:23:13,560
and the Chinese merchants will get 49 percent.

495
00:23:14,000 --> 00:23:16,480
All the Chinese merchant representatives here

496
00:23:16,480 --> 00:23:18,560
are filled with indignation.

497
00:23:19,640 --> 00:23:20,960
These past few months,

498
00:23:21,400 --> 00:23:24,800
I've been running between the General Chamber of Commerce, the Shanghai Municipal Council, and Hongkou.

499
00:23:24,800 --> 00:23:26,200
Bouncing between these three places,

500
00:23:26,200 --> 00:23:28,060
I've completely worn myself out.

501
00:23:29,080 --> 00:23:30,610
That's outright banditry.

502
00:23:30,920 --> 00:23:33,240
Behind the Japanese navy, army,

503
00:23:33,560 --> 00:23:34,890
and political circles,

504
00:23:35,080 --> 00:23:36,680
there is a long string of

505
00:23:36,800 --> 00:23:39,000
Japanese plutocrats and businessmen.

506
00:23:39,200 --> 00:23:41,520
They are fighting each other tooth and nail

507
00:23:41,520 --> 00:23:42,920
to grab these factories.

508
00:23:43,320 --> 00:23:46,580
How could they spit out the prize they've already claimed?

509
00:23:46,680 --> 00:23:48,200
and spit it back out?

510
00:23:49,120 --> 00:23:52,640
Many of them are foreign enterprises.

511
00:23:52,880 --> 00:23:56,200
Every time the Shanghai Municipal Council negotiates,

512
00:23:56,480 --> 00:23:58,340
the Japanese just delay and deny.

513
00:23:58,520 --> 00:24:00,760
They know the international community

514
00:24:01,040 --> 00:24:04,040
is appeasing the invasion of China.

515
00:24:04,600 --> 00:24:06,920
No government is willing

516
00:24:07,320 --> 00:24:09,560
to truly fall out with Japan over this.

517
00:24:10,200 --> 00:24:11,200
That makes sense.

518
00:24:11,760 --> 00:24:12,640
Mr. Shao.

519
00:24:12,760 --> 00:24:14,600
You are highly respected.

520
00:24:14,960 --> 00:24:16,280
If you make a call,

521
00:24:16,680 --> 00:24:18,520
you can unite the people

522
00:24:18,640 --> 00:24:19,680
in our business community.

523
00:24:19,680 --> 00:24:21,240
We'll sign a joint petition.

524
00:24:21,240 --> 00:24:23,520
If necessary, we'll go on strikes

525
00:24:23,880 --> 00:24:26,240
to pressure the Shanghai Municipal Council.

526
00:24:26,240 --> 00:24:27,240
What do you think?

527
00:24:28,440 --> 00:24:31,120
Mr. Brown will be willing to help us

528
00:24:33,880 --> 00:24:35,540
negotiate with the Japanese.

529
00:24:35,680 --> 00:24:38,720
The Shanghai Municipal Council needs to have cards to play.

530
00:24:38,720 --> 00:24:40,520
After all, Japan doesn't want to

531
00:24:40,720 --> 00:24:43,440
fall out with Britain, the US, and France.

532
00:24:45,640 --> 00:24:46,600
Mr. Shao.

533
00:24:47,520 --> 00:24:49,800
The approach of Mr. Brown and Ruisheng

534
00:24:50,720 --> 00:24:53,280
is the only feasible way right now.

535
00:24:53,880 --> 00:24:56,640
It seems Hechen has thought deeply

536
00:24:57,320 --> 00:24:59,760
about this matter.

537
00:25:08,320 --> 00:25:09,980
Sweet and Sour Mandarin Fish.

538
00:25:12,960 --> 00:25:14,640
Three-Layer Duck.

539
00:25:17,280 --> 00:25:19,640
Braised Pork Ball in Crab Roe Soup.

540
00:25:20,640 --> 00:25:22,440
Boiled Shredded Dried Tofu.

541
00:25:24,680 --> 00:25:28,400
Hechen's Huaiyang chef is quite skilled.

542
00:25:29,360 --> 00:25:30,880
I have heard of it.

543
00:25:31,640 --> 00:25:32,170
Mr. Shao,

544
00:25:32,400 --> 00:25:34,860
I also prepared some Northern dishes today.

545
00:25:35,600 --> 00:25:36,600
Hechen,

546
00:25:37,080 --> 00:25:38,410
thanks for the trouble.

547
00:25:38,480 --> 00:25:40,040
Let's start.

548
00:25:42,400 --> 00:25:43,440
Mr. Shao.

549
00:25:57,880 --> 00:25:58,600
Miss Sibao.

550
00:25:59,280 --> 00:26:00,320
Come.

551
00:26:02,280 --> 00:26:03,720
How was the food earlier?

552
00:26:03,840 --> 00:26:04,920
It was excellent.

553
00:26:05,280 --> 00:26:06,720
President Shao is really amazing.

554
00:26:06,720 --> 00:26:08,440
He can tell the heat and ingredients just by tasting.

555
00:26:08,440 --> 00:26:09,960
He said your dishes

556
00:26:12,400 --> 00:26:13,530
are very authentic.

557
00:26:15,640 --> 00:26:16,520
A gourmet

558
00:26:16,720 --> 00:26:18,200
naturally knows what's good or bad.

559
00:26:18,200 --> 00:26:19,320
Yes.

560
00:26:20,600 --> 00:26:22,800
If I knew someone was so slow,

561
00:26:23,200 --> 00:26:25,160
I would have gone to help him.

562
00:26:36,520 --> 00:26:39,720
People always say to resist the war to the end.

563
00:26:40,880 --> 00:26:42,040
What is the end?

564
00:26:42,880 --> 00:26:43,960
Where is the end?

565
00:26:44,600 --> 00:26:46,360
After thinking twice,

566
00:26:46,960 --> 00:26:50,360
I negotiated with the Japanese for a long time.

567
00:26:50,840 --> 00:26:53,800
The Japanese side decided to reorganize the municipal government,

568
00:26:53,800 --> 00:26:57,000
renaming it the Shanghai Special Municipal Government.

569
00:26:57,200 --> 00:26:59,480
The municipal government has ten bureaus.

570
00:26:59,480 --> 00:27:01,160
The Japanese won't interfere at all

571
00:27:01,160 --> 00:27:03,240
with the selection of the directors.

572
00:27:03,760 --> 00:27:05,320
All these conditions

573
00:27:05,840 --> 00:27:09,360
are what we fought back from the Japanese.

574
00:27:11,600 --> 00:27:12,680
Hechen,

575
00:27:13,240 --> 00:27:15,480
you've always had a chivalrous spirit,

576
00:27:15,840 --> 00:27:18,840
unlike those who talk empty words.

577
00:27:19,480 --> 00:27:22,000
Could you come and help me?

578
00:27:22,920 --> 00:27:23,880
Mr. Shao,

579
00:27:24,400 --> 00:27:25,600
my chivalrous spirit

580
00:27:25,680 --> 00:27:27,840
is just about liking to read martial arts novels,

581
00:27:27,840 --> 00:27:29,120
and watching movies

582
00:27:29,480 --> 00:27:31,880
like 'The Burning of the Red Lotus Temple'.

583
00:27:32,080 --> 00:27:33,440
First, I have no fame.

584
00:27:33,760 --> 00:27:35,560
Second, I'm greedy for money.

585
00:27:36,280 --> 00:27:38,360
Third, I'm afraid of death.

586
00:27:39,080 --> 00:27:40,210
I really can't do it.

587
00:27:40,400 --> 00:27:41,080
Mr. Shao.

588
00:27:41,280 --> 00:27:44,120
The nation is in peril, stop being so modest.

589
00:27:44,440 --> 00:27:45,920
If we don't step forward,

590
00:27:46,080 --> 00:27:48,600
who else will?

591
00:27:49,000 --> 00:27:51,280
To make a contribution

592
00:27:51,640 --> 00:27:53,170
to Shanghai's livelihood.

593
00:27:54,280 --> 00:27:55,680
What contribution?

594
00:27:56,200 --> 00:27:58,840
The shameful things traitors do

595
00:27:59,320 --> 00:28:01,850
can be described in such a high-sounding way.

596
00:28:01,920 --> 00:28:04,760
I have truly experienced it today.

597
00:28:05,720 --> 00:28:06,980
High-sounding or not,

598
00:28:07,240 --> 00:28:09,100
it's sharing the nation's burden

599
00:28:09,400 --> 00:28:10,960
out of necessity.

600
00:28:12,080 --> 00:28:13,160
In contrast,

601
00:28:14,040 --> 00:28:15,240
those who only talk about patriotism

602
00:28:15,240 --> 00:28:17,240
rarely end up well.

603
00:28:17,960 --> 00:28:20,680
I specially invited Mr. Lin today.

604
00:28:22,040 --> 00:28:23,440
We are all our own people,

605
00:28:23,640 --> 00:28:25,080
so I won't hide anything.

606
00:28:26,520 --> 00:28:27,440
Mr. Lin

607
00:28:27,440 --> 00:28:30,920
is a professionally trained talent.

608
00:28:31,360 --> 00:28:33,840
From Chongqing to Hong Kong,

609
00:28:34,240 --> 00:28:36,120
he made his way back to Shanghai

610
00:28:36,560 --> 00:28:39,280
and is starting a great enterprise.

611
00:28:39,760 --> 00:28:42,200
Although Mr. Lin is young,

612
00:28:42,520 --> 00:28:44,680
he is a hero of the underworld.

613
00:28:45,440 --> 00:28:47,720
He has many talented subordinates,

614
00:28:48,160 --> 00:28:50,760
enough to contend with the Chongqing faction.

615
00:28:51,280 --> 00:28:52,520
As for safety issues,

616
00:28:54,440 --> 00:28:55,770
you don't need to worry.

617
00:28:56,000 --> 00:28:57,200
Mr. Shao flatters me.

618
00:28:57,440 --> 00:28:58,360
I think that

619
00:28:58,720 --> 00:29:00,720
those sent by Chongqing,

620
00:29:00,840 --> 00:29:02,520
the so-called patriots,

621
00:29:03,800 --> 00:29:06,000
are running amok in the concession.

622
00:29:06,440 --> 00:29:08,240
They label whoever they dislike

623
00:29:08,920 --> 00:29:11,240
as a traitor.

624
00:29:11,880 --> 00:29:12,880
They either kill,

625
00:29:13,040 --> 00:29:13,720
kidnap,

626
00:29:14,320 --> 00:29:15,240
or extort them.

627
00:29:16,200 --> 00:29:19,660
As the saying goes, give someone a taste of their own medicine.

628
00:29:19,720 --> 00:29:22,320
Desperate times call for desperate measures.

629
00:29:22,360 --> 00:29:23,640
Since the Japanese

630
00:29:23,920 --> 00:29:27,120
can't do anything about these terrorists in the concession,

631
00:29:27,120 --> 00:29:28,280
then I believe that

632
00:29:29,640 --> 00:29:31,200
only special means

633
00:29:31,600 --> 00:29:33,640
can achieve our desired goal.

634
00:29:35,480 --> 00:29:39,640
It's a good business indeed.

635
00:29:40,280 --> 00:29:41,440
Outlaw heroes

636
00:29:41,960 --> 00:29:43,620
fighting in the martial world

637
00:29:43,800 --> 00:29:46,480
can still leave behind the Water Margin.

638
00:29:46,880 --> 00:29:48,120
May I ask Mr. Lin,

639
00:29:48,760 --> 00:29:50,600
by doing this business with you,

640
00:29:51,200 --> 00:29:52,960
what will be left behind?

641
00:30:12,880 --> 00:30:14,120
Mr. Gu died

642
00:30:15,440 --> 00:30:16,800
in the hospital.

643
00:30:23,760 --> 00:30:25,280
Mr. Gu is gone.

644
00:30:27,680 --> 00:30:29,280
Did Mr. Gu pass away?

645
00:30:30,440 --> 00:30:32,360
Hechen, before I came here,

646
00:30:32,520 --> 00:30:34,720
I just went to the hospital to see Mr. Gu.

647
00:30:34,840 --> 00:30:37,640
He was holding my hand and talking to me.

648
00:30:38,600 --> 00:30:39,240
What?

649
00:30:39,520 --> 00:30:41,400
In just a moment, Mr. Gu is...

650
00:30:47,080 --> 00:30:50,320
Is Mr. Gu gone?

651
00:30:52,120 --> 00:30:53,600
Mr. Gu!

652
00:30:57,920 --> 00:30:59,600
Mr. Gu.

653
00:31:00,840 --> 00:31:03,120
I have established

654
00:31:03,280 --> 00:31:05,160
the Special Operations Division at No. 67, Daxi Road.

655
00:31:05,160 --> 00:31:06,600
If you need anything,

656
00:31:07,000 --> 00:31:09,400
I am willing to serve you with utmost loyalty.

657
00:31:09,400 --> 00:31:10,600
Stop it.

658
00:31:11,240 --> 00:31:12,370
Coercion by swords,

659
00:31:12,880 --> 00:31:14,160
spy tactics.

660
00:31:14,760 --> 00:31:16,090
Do you think I, Jin Qiwu,

661
00:31:16,320 --> 00:31:18,400
a dignified man,

662
00:31:18,760 --> 00:31:20,160
would be afraid of them?

663
00:31:25,360 --> 00:31:25,960
Mr. Jin,

664
00:31:27,840 --> 00:31:28,840
my condolences.

665
00:31:31,520 --> 00:31:32,440
Mr. Gu's death

666
00:31:32,880 --> 00:31:35,320
was caused by grenade shrapnel.

667
00:31:37,040 --> 00:31:38,880
It went from his back through his chest.

668
00:31:38,880 --> 00:31:40,280
We have caught the man.

669
00:31:40,760 --> 00:31:41,960
He's from Chongqing,

670
00:31:43,440 --> 00:31:44,840
named Jiang Shougen.

671
00:31:45,760 --> 00:31:46,960
He is in my custody.

672
00:31:47,760 --> 00:31:49,400
If you want revenge, Mr. Jin,

673
00:31:49,880 --> 00:31:51,340
you can come to me anytime.

674
00:31:51,600 --> 00:31:52,720
It's too late.

675
00:31:53,080 --> 00:31:54,320
Too late.

676
00:31:55,560 --> 00:31:56,120
Mr. Gu.

677
00:31:56,120 --> 00:31:56,880
From now on,

678
00:31:58,960 --> 00:32:00,960
if they kill one of our businessmen,

679
00:32:01,160 --> 00:32:02,560
I will kill one of theirs.

680
00:32:03,600 --> 00:32:05,400
If they kill one of our scholars,

681
00:32:05,720 --> 00:32:07,320
I will kill one of theirs.

682
00:32:07,640 --> 00:32:08,840
To put on a rival show,

683
00:32:09,040 --> 00:32:10,840
let's see who can sing to the end.

684
00:32:11,640 --> 00:32:12,480
Mr. Jin,

685
00:32:12,680 --> 00:32:13,520
well,

686
00:32:14,600 --> 00:32:16,260
let me tell you some good news.

687
00:32:16,960 --> 00:32:18,280
The blue-eyed Persian cat

688
00:32:18,280 --> 00:32:21,000
that you lost a few days ago

689
00:32:22,240 --> 00:32:23,800
was found by my men.

690
00:32:24,040 --> 00:32:25,680
It has been sent to your home.

691
00:32:28,160 --> 00:32:29,400
Chanel?

692
00:32:30,960 --> 00:32:32,800
My Chanel is found?

693
00:32:33,160 --> 00:32:35,640
She was lost for three days.

694
00:32:37,560 --> 00:32:39,520
Chanel is found?

695
00:32:39,680 --> 00:32:41,600
Found?

696
00:32:45,680 --> 00:32:47,760
Mr. Lin, you are indeed resourceful.

697
00:32:48,560 --> 00:32:50,680
Please

698
00:32:51,480 --> 00:32:53,940
keep an eye on our Jixiang Ruyi in the future.

699
00:32:54,320 --> 00:32:55,360
It's the wolfhound

700
00:32:55,360 --> 00:32:57,480
I've raised since it was little.

701
00:32:58,280 --> 00:32:59,920
While walking a couple of days ago,

702
00:32:59,920 --> 00:33:02,250
it was almost seduced away by a female dog.

703
00:33:02,600 --> 00:33:03,660
I am quite worried.

704
00:33:04,200 --> 00:33:05,160
Don't worry.

705
00:33:05,600 --> 00:33:07,640
In the future, for anything regarding the Tian Mansion,

706
00:33:07,640 --> 00:33:09,240
I will attend to every detail

707
00:33:10,000 --> 00:33:11,930
and serve you with utmost loyalty.

708
00:33:12,440 --> 00:33:13,920
Thank you.

709
00:33:19,160 --> 00:33:20,420
Mr. Gu has passed away.

710
00:33:21,080 --> 00:33:22,940
Let us raise our glasses together

711
00:33:23,440 --> 00:33:24,480
to express our condolences.

712
00:33:24,480 --> 00:33:24,960
Come.

713
00:33:52,720 --> 00:33:53,920
To Mr. Gu.

714
00:34:09,440 --> 00:34:10,480
Is the northern dish here?

715
00:34:10,480 --> 00:34:11,480
Yes.

716
00:34:18,000 --> 00:34:18,960
What is it?

717
00:34:19,360 --> 00:34:22,360
This is called the Four Beginnings of Meng's Mansion.

718
00:34:24,360 --> 00:34:26,889
I didn't remember everything Chef Meng said.

719
00:34:26,960 --> 00:34:28,960
Four Beginnings of Meng's Mansion.

720
00:34:30,880 --> 00:34:32,880
Four Beginnings of Meng's Mansion.

721
00:34:33,280 --> 00:34:34,719
Men have these Four Beginnings

722
00:34:34,719 --> 00:34:36,199
just as they have their four limbs.

723
00:34:36,199 --> 00:34:38,360
Thus it's called the Four Beginnings of Meng's Mansion.

724
00:34:38,360 --> 00:34:41,090
This is the first dish of the Meng Family Banquet.

725
00:34:41,280 --> 00:34:43,940
What are the Four Beginnings of Meng's Mansion?

726
00:34:44,360 --> 00:34:45,280
Mr. Brown.

727
00:34:45,480 --> 00:34:47,920
The Four Beginnings refer to the four virtues:

728
00:34:47,920 --> 00:34:49,179
a sense of compassion,

729
00:34:49,480 --> 00:34:50,560
a sense of shame,

730
00:34:50,880 --> 00:34:52,080
the sense of modesty and courtesy,

731
00:34:52,080 --> 00:34:53,639
and the sense of right and wrong.

732
00:34:53,639 --> 00:34:57,880
They correspond to benevolence, righteousness, propriety, and wisdom.

733
00:34:58,600 --> 00:35:00,080
Yes.

734
00:35:01,080 --> 00:35:02,120
Mr. Shao,

735
00:35:02,160 --> 00:35:03,120
Mr. Lin.

736
00:35:03,680 --> 00:35:06,160
I was overcome with sorrow just now,

737
00:35:06,960 --> 00:35:08,220
and lost my composure.

738
00:35:10,640 --> 00:35:11,440
It's fine.

739
00:35:11,640 --> 00:35:14,570
Actually, after hearing Mr. Shao's remarks just now

740
00:35:14,720 --> 00:35:17,580
about joining the Great Way Municipal Government,

741
00:35:18,040 --> 00:35:20,320
I deeply understand Mr. Shao's

742
00:35:21,840 --> 00:35:23,120
good intentions.

743
00:35:23,760 --> 00:35:25,690
I also had a realization, Mr. Shao.

744
00:35:26,200 --> 00:35:27,160
As human beings,

745
00:35:27,720 --> 00:35:29,600
where should our responsibilities lie?

746
00:35:29,600 --> 00:35:30,240
Mr. Shao,

747
00:35:30,640 --> 00:35:33,000
benevolence, righteousness, propriety, and wisdom.

748
00:35:33,000 --> 00:35:34,080
I toast to you.

749
00:35:38,920 --> 00:35:39,720
Mr. Lin.

750
00:35:45,280 --> 00:35:46,680
What kind of fish is this?

751
00:35:47,760 --> 00:35:50,220
This dish is called Lingzhao Mandarin Fish.

752
00:35:50,440 --> 00:35:52,560
Back then, King Wen of Zhou shared his joy with the people,

753
00:35:52,560 --> 00:35:53,440
and was loved by them.

754
00:35:53,440 --> 00:35:55,500
He called the pond the Numinous Pond.

755
00:35:55,600 --> 00:35:57,680
Today, all you gentlemen are here,

756
00:35:57,840 --> 00:35:59,080
making guests feel at home.

757
00:35:59,080 --> 00:36:00,800
The more, the merrier.

758
00:36:01,080 --> 00:36:02,320
It perfectly fits this scene.

759
00:36:02,320 --> 00:36:04,920
So this dish is called Lingzhao Mandarin Fish.

760
00:36:08,840 --> 00:36:09,640
Is there more?

761
00:36:10,400 --> 00:36:11,120
Yes.

762
00:36:11,240 --> 00:36:11,900
Right away.

763
00:36:13,920 --> 00:36:15,180
Mr. Shao, have a taste.

764
00:36:16,480 --> 00:36:17,000
Please.

765
00:36:25,560 --> 00:36:28,240
This saying is quite fresh.

766
00:36:29,720 --> 00:36:32,480
Speaking of the more, the merrier,

767
00:36:32,880 --> 00:36:36,160
what Ruisheng and Hechen suggested just now,

768
00:36:36,440 --> 00:36:38,360
to unite the business community

769
00:36:38,640 --> 00:36:40,600
and negotiate with the Japanese,

770
00:36:42,560 --> 00:36:44,280
I think it's feasible.

771
00:36:44,800 --> 00:36:45,800
To put it plainly,

772
00:36:46,160 --> 00:36:47,760
as long as we first express

773
00:36:47,920 --> 00:36:50,240
our sincerity to cooperate with the Japanese,

774
00:36:50,240 --> 00:36:52,480
the rest will be easy to talk about.

775
00:36:53,080 --> 00:36:54,240
No matter what,

776
00:36:54,680 --> 00:36:56,140
the situation in Shanghai

777
00:36:56,560 --> 00:36:59,960
requires gathering many truly patriotic

778
00:37:00,280 --> 00:37:04,000
friends who don't care about personal success or reputation

779
00:37:04,920 --> 00:37:06,240
to work together.

780
00:37:06,560 --> 00:37:09,120
The position of Director of the Administration for Industry and Commerce

781
00:37:09,120 --> 00:37:11,360
is specially reserved for you.

782
00:37:12,000 --> 00:37:13,040
The first step

783
00:37:13,360 --> 00:37:16,160
is that all factories under the Tian family's name

784
00:37:16,440 --> 00:37:19,440
must be returned to their owner in perfect condition.

785
00:37:20,600 --> 00:37:21,520
Mr. Hechen.

786
00:37:22,040 --> 00:37:24,970
What Mr. Shao said is all from the bottom of his heart.

787
00:37:25,360 --> 00:37:27,020
Thoughtful and far-sighted.

788
00:37:27,160 --> 00:37:29,220
You need to think about it carefully.

789
00:37:36,560 --> 00:37:37,360
What's wrong?

790
00:37:37,440 --> 00:37:38,440
A fish bone.

791
00:37:39,000 --> 00:37:39,860
Eat something.

792
00:37:40,160 --> 00:37:41,200
Eat this to wash it down.

793
00:37:41,200 --> 00:37:42,080
Mr. Tian.

794
00:37:53,520 --> 00:37:54,720
I think it's fine now.

795
00:37:55,480 --> 00:37:56,940
What is this dish of yours?

796
00:37:57,280 --> 00:37:58,600
This is Emperor Qianlong's

797
00:37:58,600 --> 00:38:00,600
favorite northern dessert,

798
00:38:00,600 --> 00:38:01,840
called Three Non-Stick.

799
00:38:01,840 --> 00:38:04,400
It doesn't stick to the bowl, the chopsticks, or the teeth.

800
00:38:04,400 --> 00:38:05,440
This is good.

801
00:38:06,000 --> 00:38:07,000
Three Non-Stick.

802
00:38:07,080 --> 00:38:08,210
The name is good too.

803
00:38:09,160 --> 00:38:10,120
Sweet and soft,

804
00:38:10,520 --> 00:38:12,180
with no sticky feeling at all.

805
00:38:12,280 --> 00:38:13,540
It lives up to its name.

806
00:38:14,040 --> 00:38:15,200
You cook well.

807
00:38:15,760 --> 00:38:17,400
And you speak well too.

808
00:38:17,800 --> 00:38:18,800
You are educated.

809
00:38:18,800 --> 00:38:19,160
Thank you, Mr. Tian.

810
00:38:19,160 --> 00:38:20,480
Hechen.

811
00:38:21,480 --> 00:38:24,120
You don't have to change the subject.

812
00:38:24,520 --> 00:38:26,000
The question just now,

813
00:38:26,720 --> 00:38:29,000
you haven't given me an answer yet.

814
00:38:31,720 --> 00:38:33,520
Mr. Shao, I am not changing the subject.

815
00:38:33,520 --> 00:38:35,480
A fishbone just happened to get stuck here.

816
00:38:35,480 --> 00:38:37,360
This bite of food

817
00:38:37,760 --> 00:38:38,640
went down smoothly.

818
00:38:38,640 --> 00:38:39,960
It slid down smoothly.

819
00:38:40,080 --> 00:38:41,120
Hechen.

820
00:38:41,600 --> 00:38:45,440
The treacherous situation in The Bund right now

821
00:38:45,960 --> 00:38:47,720
is not a fishbone.

822
00:38:48,080 --> 00:38:50,010
It cannot be easily swallowed down

823
00:38:50,040 --> 00:38:54,000
with a bite of Three Non-Stick.

824
00:38:55,200 --> 00:38:56,320
I see.

825
00:38:57,400 --> 00:38:59,200
Mr. Shao's earnest intentions,

826
00:38:59,880 --> 00:39:01,320
Mr. Lin's kindness,

827
00:39:02,240 --> 00:39:04,640
I have taken them to heart.

828
00:39:05,440 --> 00:39:07,240
Try this Three Non-Stick. Come.

829
00:39:07,560 --> 00:39:08,320
Okay.

830
00:39:09,120 --> 00:39:09,800
Come.

831
00:39:28,320 --> 00:39:29,520
Return San's sister's comb

832
00:39:29,520 --> 00:39:30,480
yourself.

833
00:39:31,280 --> 00:39:33,200
If I do it myself, it's not returning.

834
00:39:33,200 --> 00:39:34,600
It's giving.

835
00:39:37,280 --> 00:39:38,160
Lad,

836
00:39:38,160 --> 00:39:39,490
what's your name again?

837
00:39:39,640 --> 00:39:40,570
Yang Yuanzheng.

838
00:39:40,680 --> 00:39:42,120
You are really something.

839
00:39:42,120 --> 00:39:43,580
In front of so many people,

840
00:39:43,640 --> 00:39:44,840
you dared to pull a grenade.

841
00:39:44,840 --> 00:39:46,560
Don't be foolish again.

842
00:39:47,720 --> 00:39:48,480
But you know,

843
00:39:48,840 --> 00:39:52,240
the moment you stood in front of me to block the grenade,

844
00:39:52,800 --> 00:39:54,400
I thought you were a real man.

845
00:39:54,680 --> 00:39:56,680
Weren't you afraid

846
00:39:57,160 --> 00:39:59,040
he would actually pull the grenade?

847
00:39:59,040 --> 00:40:00,440
He doesn't have the guts.

848
00:40:00,760 --> 00:40:01,400
He wouldn't dare.

849
00:40:01,400 --> 00:40:02,040
If he pulled it,

850
00:40:02,040 --> 00:40:03,570
I would have kicked it away.

851
00:40:03,640 --> 00:40:05,570
I even figured out where to kick it.

852
00:40:05,960 --> 00:40:07,820
The Battalion Commander is gone.

853
00:40:11,000 --> 00:40:12,880
I couldn't save him.

854
00:40:17,240 --> 00:40:18,280
Buddy, get up.

855
00:40:21,240 --> 00:40:22,720
All right, don't be sad.

856
00:40:23,200 --> 00:40:24,960
Look at these brothers now.

857
00:40:25,240 --> 00:40:26,100
Everyone here,

858
00:40:26,160 --> 00:40:28,240
who hasn't survived a pile of dead bodies?

859
00:40:28,240 --> 00:40:30,040
You lost a Battalion Commander,

860
00:40:30,240 --> 00:40:31,960
but you gained us brothers.

861
00:40:32,440 --> 00:40:33,800
We are a family.

862
00:40:34,360 --> 00:40:35,440
Don't cry.

863
00:40:44,840 --> 00:40:46,040
You wily old soldier,

864
00:40:46,120 --> 00:40:47,680
how did you wander to Wuhan again?

865
00:40:47,680 --> 00:40:48,680
When we parted last time,

866
00:40:48,680 --> 00:40:49,610
didn't I tell you

867
00:40:49,640 --> 00:40:50,840
that I would come find you?

868
00:40:50,840 --> 00:40:52,560
Did you think we were joking?

869
00:40:52,880 --> 00:40:54,720
I promised the brothers.

870
00:40:54,880 --> 00:40:55,760
With your skills,

871
00:40:55,760 --> 00:40:57,480
you'll be a high official sooner or later.

872
00:40:57,480 --> 00:40:58,640
So when we retreated,

873
00:40:58,640 --> 00:40:59,720
everyone followed me.

874
00:40:59,720 --> 00:41:00,560
We hid and dodged

875
00:41:00,560 --> 00:41:02,400
all the way here.

876
00:41:02,720 --> 00:41:03,980
Once we entered Wuhan,

877
00:41:04,240 --> 00:41:05,960
there were Gendarmerie everywhere.

878
00:41:05,960 --> 00:41:07,680
Thanks to my brother's cleverness.

879
00:41:07,680 --> 00:41:09,680
Brother, what did you say at that time?

880
00:41:09,680 --> 00:41:10,810
I told the brothers,

881
00:41:11,320 --> 00:41:12,720
if you want to stay alive,

882
00:41:13,040 --> 00:41:14,440
where is the safest place?

883
00:41:14,440 --> 00:41:17,040
Based on my over ten years of battlefield experience,

884
00:41:17,040 --> 00:41:20,160
only military hospitals are the safest.

885
00:41:20,760 --> 00:41:22,080
The brothers all have wounds, right?

886
00:41:22,080 --> 00:41:22,840
Yes, we did.

887
00:41:22,960 --> 00:41:23,360
Right? Yes.

888
00:41:23,360 --> 00:41:23,840
Right.

889
00:41:23,920 --> 00:41:25,720
Wounds are our passes.

890
00:41:25,800 --> 00:41:26,840
As long as you get into the hospital,

891
00:41:26,840 --> 00:41:28,480
you'll get good food, drinks and treatment,

892
00:41:28,480 --> 00:41:31,080
as well as pretty little nurses.

893
00:41:32,320 --> 00:41:32,880
So,

894
00:41:33,080 --> 00:41:35,400
we searched the whole world for this military hospital,

895
00:41:35,400 --> 00:41:36,480
but ran into Japs.

896
00:41:36,920 --> 00:41:39,120
So Liao got such a big pass.

897
00:41:39,480 --> 00:41:40,640
Just to find you,

898
00:41:41,040 --> 00:41:42,320
we walked through the gates of hell.

899
00:41:42,320 --> 00:41:44,280
What do you mean by walked through the gates of hell?

900
00:41:44,280 --> 00:41:47,000
You mean walked around the gates of hell.

901
00:41:48,880 --> 00:41:49,960
I have nine lives.

902
00:41:50,480 --> 00:41:51,410
Wherever I walk,

903
00:41:51,600 --> 00:41:53,200
no matter how many times, I am not afraid.

904
00:41:53,200 --> 00:41:55,040
But from now on, we won't mention this anymore.

905
00:41:55,040 --> 00:41:56,840
Just pretend it never happened.

906
00:41:57,640 --> 00:41:58,720
Anyway,

907
00:41:58,840 --> 00:42:00,280
we found the person in the hospital.

908
00:42:00,280 --> 00:42:01,680
That proves I was right.

909
00:42:01,880 --> 00:42:02,440
Right?

910
00:42:02,880 --> 00:42:03,480
Yes.

911
00:42:03,960 --> 00:42:05,000
Let's talk business.

912
00:42:05,000 --> 00:42:06,200
Let's talk business.

913
00:42:07,560 --> 00:42:09,960
You came all the way from Xuzhou to Wuhan,

914
00:42:10,120 --> 00:42:11,520
taking such a big detour,

915
00:42:11,640 --> 00:42:13,720
and you even gave up clearing your name.

916
00:42:13,720 --> 00:42:15,080
What were you thinking?

917
00:42:15,560 --> 00:42:16,560
What was I thinking?

918
00:42:16,560 --> 00:42:18,120
I gave up, and that's it.

919
00:42:18,920 --> 00:42:20,450
Anyway, I let you guys down.

920
00:42:20,480 --> 00:42:21,480
You came from far away to find me,

921
00:42:21,480 --> 00:42:22,560
and now I'm nothing,

922
00:42:22,560 --> 00:42:24,020
and I even got you injured.

923
00:42:24,600 --> 00:42:25,240
I'm sorry.

924
00:42:25,400 --> 00:42:26,800
What do you mean by that?

925
00:42:27,680 --> 00:42:30,520
We buddies know exactly what kind of person you are.

926
00:42:30,520 --> 00:42:32,450
Everyone came all this way for you,

927
00:42:32,600 --> 00:42:33,280
hoping

928
00:42:33,520 --> 00:42:34,400
you'd lead us

929
00:42:34,640 --> 00:42:36,440
to make something of ourselves again.

930
00:42:36,440 --> 00:42:37,040
Right?

931
00:42:37,360 --> 00:42:38,480
Yeah, it's settled.

932
00:42:38,480 --> 00:42:39,810
We've all discussed it.

933
00:42:45,560 --> 00:42:46,560
Then...

934
00:42:47,520 --> 00:42:49,760
Can I come with you?

935
00:42:52,800 --> 00:42:53,800
Sure.

936
00:42:54,240 --> 00:42:56,170
You're good at throwing grenades.

937
00:42:57,880 --> 00:43:00,040
Just don't throw them at us anymore.
